In LXX. we find μακρόθυμος of God Exod. xxxiv. 6, Ps. ciii. 8 3 of man Prov. xiv. 29, xvi. 32, xix. ll. The word is rare in Classical Greek, but- μακροθυμία occurs in Menander p. 203 Mein, and μακροθυμέω in Plutarch. On the relation of μακροθυμία to ὑπομονή see Lightfoot on Col. i. 11, and 2 Tim. iii. 11.
